* {{l|ja|機に|tr=[[機に因って法を説く]], ''[[ki ni yotte hō o toku]]''}}: to change the [[message]] to [[suit]] one's [[audience]]: to [[alter]] the [[format]] or [[presentation]] for better [[acceptance]], without changing the [[core]] [[idea]]s being [[convey]]ed
* {{l|ja|機を逸する|tr=[[きをいっする]], ''[[ki o issuru]]''}}, {{l|ja|機を失する|tr=[[きをいしっする]], ''[[ki o shissuru]]''}}: to [[miss the boat]], to [[miss out]]

===Etymology 2===
Alteration from こうべうち, itself a compound of {{l|ja|首|tr=''kōbe'', "head"}} + {{l|ja|打ち|tr=''uchi'', "striking, hitting"}}.

====Noun====
{{ja-noun|k|hira=こぶち|rom=kobuchi}}

# a [[trap]] or [[snare]] that works by [[behead]]ing the [[bird]] or [[beast]] caught in it

===Etymology 3===
From [[onomatopoeic]] {{l|ja|はた|tr=''hata''}}, possibly for the sound of the shuttle running back and forth, or for the sound of a woven cloth moving in the wind (c.f. {{l|ja|旗|tr=''hata'', "a flag"}}).

====Noun====
{{ja-noun|k|hira=はた|rom=hata}}

# a [[loom]]
# [[woven]] [[cloth]]

===Etymology 4===
Stem form ({{l|ja|連用形}}) of the verb {{l|ja|機る|tr=''wakatsuru''|gloss=to [[manipulate]] something}}, itself an alteration of {{l|ja|誘る|tr=''okotsuru''|gloss=to [[manipulate]] or [[con]] someone}}, a compound of {{l|ja|痴|tr=''oko''|gloss=a fool}} + {{l|ja|釣る|tr=''tsuru''|gloss=to [[fish]], to [[draw out]]}}.

# to [[manipulate]] {{qualifier|as in a device}}
# to [[manipulate]] {{qualifier|as in a person}}: to [[deceive]], to [[take in]] someone
# to get on someone's right side; to [[humor]] someone; to [[make an effort]] to [[please]] someone

